Key Insights

Overall Performance

The platform generated over ₦2 million in total revenue with an average order value of ₦778.49.

A total of 3,000 customer orders were analyzed, representing a diverse mix of regions and income levels.

-- Product & Category Performance

Food & Beverages emerged as the top-performing category, followed by Electronics and Home Appliances.

These categories collectively drive the bulk of sales, suggesting strong consumer demand for essential and lifestyle products.

-- Regional Sales Analysis

The East and South regions lead in total revenue, indicating higher sales engagement and purchasing power in these areas.

The West region follows closely, presenting opportunities for market expansion and localized promotions.

-- Customer Demographics

Spending is almost evenly split by gender — Male (49.79%) and Female (50.21%) — showing balanced participation across demographics.

This balance indicates that gender-based targeting may not be as effective as category or region-based strategies.

-- Behavioral Patterns

Mid-income customers (₦40K–₦80K) show higher purchasing activity, often buying in greater quantities per order.

As income increases, the number of items purchased per order decreases, but overall order value tends to rise — indicating a premium purchasing pattern among higher-income customers.

-- High-Value Customer Segments

Customers aged 35–54 and those in Doctor and Manager occupations contribute the most to revenue.

These groups represent high-value targets for retention programs and premium product marketing.

-- Country-Level Trends

Sales distribution shows activity across multiple global markets, with strong performance in African and European regions.

-- Strategic Recommendations

Expand marketing in East & South regions to maintain strong momentum.

Develop premium campaigns targeting high-income and professional customers.

Bundle popular items like Food & Beverages and Electronics for mid-income segments to increase basket size.

Maintain balanced marketing across genders, focusing on product preference instead.

 -- Tools Used: Power BI (Data Modeling, DAX, Visualization)
 -- Dataset: 3,000 Jumia Customer Orders
 -- Goal: Identify sales trends, customer insights, and data-driven opportunities for strategic planning.
